                                     },
                       "message":  "EDITOR-WINDOW-TITLE: reflect open scene + dirty state in title bar\n\nSurface the in-app Save state in the window title — e.g.\n\"level.rge-scene * — RGE Editor\" (asterisk = unsaved). The editor tracks a\nscene_source_path (#269) and a Command-Bus dirty flag, but the winit title\nwas a static \"RGE Editor\". Pure editor-shell; no binary change.\n\n- New lifecycle/window_title.rs: pure editor_window_title(scene_source_path,\n  is_dirty) -\u003e String (the only logic, headless-testable) +\n  EditorShell::sync_window_title, which pushes it to the window via set_title\n  only on change (tracked by a new last_window_title field); no-op headless.\n- mod.rs: sync_window_title is reconciled once per frame from the\n  WindowEvent::RedrawRequested branch; last_window_title field + inits.\n\nMirrors the binary\u0027s glb_watcher_action / sync_glb_watcher pure-decision +\nreconcile pattern. +6 headless tests (4 format cases + file-name-not-path +\nwindowless no-op).\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e",
