                       "committer":  {
                                         "name":  "drhalilmurattasci",
                                         "email":  "drhalilmurattasci@users.noreply.github.com",
                                         "date":  "2026-05-30T06:38:53Z"
                                     },
                       "message":  "EDITOR-WINDOW-TITLE: reset title cache on window install (post-exec fix)\n\nPost-exec correction. last_window_title caches the title last handed to\nset_title, but it survived a window replacement: on suspend/resume,\ninit_render_state creates a new winit window at the static creation title\n(\"RGE Editor\") while the cache still held the previous dynamic title, so the\nnext sync_window_title saw cached == desired and skipped set_title, leaving\nthe new window mistitled.\n\nFix: reset self.last_window_title = None immediately after\nself.window = Some(window) in render_path.rs, so the next reconcile detects\na change and re-applies the live title. rg confirms a single window-install\nsite, so the one reset fully covers it.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e",
                       "tree":  {
